      "rationale": "Blood analog viscosity (3.45 ± 0.12 mPa·s), density (1050 ± 5 kg/m³), inlet velocity profile (flat with ±3% turbulence intensity), and rotational speed (±15 RPM) characterized from measurement data. A screening sensitivity study was conducted during model development to rank these inputs; results indicated viscosity and rotational speed as the highest-influence parameters. Uncertainty propagation via Latin hypercube sampling (n=200) yielded NIH coefficient of variation of 6.2%, within acceptable bounds. Input uncertainty documentation meets MRL 2 requirements."
